# perimeter

- _perimeter(g)_

Answer the perimeter of the two-dimensional geometry _g_.

At `Circle`:

```
>>> Circle([0 0], 1)
>>> .perimeter
2.pi
```

At `Rectangle`:

```
>>> Rectangle([-1 -1], [1 1])
>>> .perimeter
8
```

At `Triangle`:

```
>>> aasTriangle(1/4.pi, 1/2.pi, 1)
>>> .perimeter
1 + 2.sqrt + 1
```

